name: Rosso' Micro Roastery
description:
We are a Coffee Roastery based on Tangerang Selatan, Indonesia.

We are only provide Indonesian Coffee beans, from Aceh in North Sumatra to Papua Wamena from Papua Island.

Our Indonesian Coffee collections both Arabica & Robusta, we have almost had 30 varians of coffee from House Blend, 100% Arabica, 100% Robusta with varians of post harvest processing : Semi Washed, Fully Washed, Natural Dried & Honey Dried processing.

name: Carios
description: Welcome to "Carios," a vibrant cafe nestled in the heart of Serang City, where freshly brewed coffee mingles with the tantalizing aroma of Asian fusion cuisine. Come and step inside to discover a cozy yet modern atmosphere suitable for working and hang-out, where skilled baristas craft an array of specialty coffees from local suppliers, complemented by a menu featuring ayam goreng sambal matah, Sukiyaki-don, chicken sesame salad, and others delicious dishes. Whether you need a caffeine fix or are craving an innovative culinary Carios, we invite you to indulge in the perfect blend of flavors and ambiance.

name: Oddy's Rawa Buntu BSD
description:
Oddy's - RESTO dan cafe estetik dan instagrammable di BSD, Tangerang. Ragam menu favorit western, oriental dan nusantara serta aneka minuman coffee dan non coffee dengan bahan terbaik.

Cafe hidden gem di BSD dengan desain industrial namun bernuansa "feels like home" memiliki area outdoor sehingga menambah kenyamanan saat menikmati hidangan ditambah dengan alunan live music setiap weekend.

Oddy's menyediakan venue & private room untuk acara keluarga (ulang tahun, pesta pernikahan, arisan dll) maupun acara kantor (meeting, training, training dll)

Lokasi strategis dan mudah dijangkau di wilayah BSD yaitu ODDYS RAWABUNTU (dekat Pasmod BSD dan Islamic Center BSD) dan ODDYS PAGEDANGAN (5 menit dari AEON Mall dan Q-Big).

Ketemulah si Oddys ini. Kebetulan lokasi resto nya juga dekat sama tujuan kita selanjutnya. Jadi kita mampir lah kesini. Tempatnya lumayan oke yah, semi outdoor gitu dan ada ruangan AC nya, dan vibesnya menenangkan sih ya gak crowd sampe gimana2 jd makan jg tenang (kt kesini skitar pk 14.00-15.00), plus sepertinya bisa karoke deh disini. Yang bikin impressive sebenarnya sama pelayanannya sih. Semua waiter dan waitress yang melayani kita itu super duper ramah. Yes, seramah itu dan murah senyum pula.    Makanan juga cepet keluarnya dan panas2 juga. Menunya lumayan banyak ya: ada iga, nasi, western, dimsum, sampe gelato juga ada. Lumayan lama buat milih2 mau makan apa. Dan setelah liat menu. Kita putusin buat pesen Sego Campur cumi tinta dan sego Ayam Lodho. Cukup enak untuk keduanya, baik cumi dan Ayam lodhonya. Kuah lodhonya enak, sambalnya jg nyaman dimakan (gak sampe kepedesan gt) jadi seperti makan ketupat / opor teksturnya. nasinya jg disajikan anget2 cocok sih berasa makan menu rumahan. Kita jg ada pesan cireng, awalnya terlihat kok oily banget ya.. tapi ternyata nggak kok, saus kecap nya rasa rujak2 gt enak. Dan di goreng dengan matang ya sampe kriuk. Overall buat first timer kesini, ini tempat yang nice sih. Cm saran aja mungkin yang indoor dikasih penerangan lbh terang yah/ mungkin perangkap nyamuk.  krn kita sempat digigitin nyamuk, walaupun gak signifikan ya . Untuk harga worth it sekali ya. Makan kenyang harga sesuai kantong untuk tempat seperti ini Thanks Oddys for filled our tummy", "published_at": "a day ago", "published_at_date": "2024-05-13 14:18:08.165217", "response_from_owner_text": "", "response_from_owner_ago": "", "response_from_owner_date": null, "review_likes_count": 1, "total_number_of_reviews_by_reviewer": 43, "total_number_of_photos_by_reviewer": 60, "is_local_guide": true, "review_translated_text": "Came here because I was confused about whether to have lunch in the BSD area, and looked for references via TikTok. Meet Oddys. Coincidentally, the location of the restaurant is also close to our next destination. So we stopped by here. The place is pretty good, its semi-outdoor and theres an AC room, and the vibes are calming, there arent too many crowds, so eating is also calm (we come here around 14.00-15.00), plus it looks like you can do karoke here. What makes it impressive is actually the service. All the waiters and waitresses who served us were super duper friendly. Yes, that friendly and smiling too.    The food also comes out quickly and is hot too. The menu is quite extensive: there are ribs, rice, western, dimsum, even gelato. It takes quite a long time to choose what to eat. And after looking at the menu. We decided to order Sego Mix squid ink and Lodho Chicken sego. Quite delicious for both, both the squid and the lodho chicken. The lodho sauce is delicious, the chili sauce is also comfortable to eat (its not too spicy) so its like eating ketupat/opor in texture. The rice is also served hot, which makes it feel like youre eating a home-cooked meal. We also ordered cireng, at first it looked really oily... but it turned out not to be, the soy sauce sauce tasted like rujak2, it was really delicious. And fried thoroughly until crispy. Overall, for first timers here, this is a nice place. name: Brewerkz
description:
A gem in the heart of BSD, our The Breeze outlet is where you could actually breathe fresher air.

Brewerkz Jakarta is a restaurant, bar and microbrewery franchise brought from Singapore. Open since 1997, the concept specializes in classic American styled food and award winning handcrafted beers and has created more than 50 different seasonal brews over its history. The beer styles range from the light and refreshing Golden Ale to a full-bodied award winning XIPA and a dark and hearty Oatmeal Stout.

name: Bebek Bengil
description: "Nestled in the enchanting surroundings of Padangtegal, Ubud, Gianyar, Bali, Indonesia, "Bebek Bengil" has been a culinary institution since its establishment in 1990. The unique origins of its name add a whimsical touch to its storied history. Legend has it that during the grand opening, a charming procession of wet ducks descended from the nearby rice fields to the road, forever etching the name "Bebek Bengil" into the annals of Bali's culinary landscape. name: John & James BSD City
description:
The best, best pizza, truly madly pasta and vegan awesomeness paired with a unique atmosphere creates an unbeatable recipe.

Once the doors open at John and James, you'll feel like you're in a typical Italian osteria, where people get together to eat really well and enjoy the company of families, friends, couples, old and young. It is a lively atmosphere, and the delicious smell of authentic Italian cuisine lingers in the air. This is an open, welcoming place, where everyone can be themselves and feel at home.

All dishes are prepared in our open-view kitchen "a la mamma". Guests experience live how passionate cooking is done the Italian way. We won't leave you hungry. Hence our motto: we love pizza - we hate expensive !

name: Burgreens The Breeze - Healthy Plant-Based Eatery
description:
Burgreens is a manifestation of a conscious eating movement that believes that what we eat directly impacts our health, animal & farmers' welfare, and environmental sustainability.

Since the very beginning, our mission is to make healthy, ethical, and sustainable food as delicious, fun, convenient, and accessible as junk food - while empowering local farmers and women through a responsible supply chain!

Anda dapat menikmati kopi favorit anda sambil bersantai maupun mengerjakan tugas kantor anda (free wifi).
